article.headline: Morehead St. 56, Tenn.-Martin 55
article.story: MARTIN, Tenn. (AP) -- Cordaryl Ballard didn't miss a shot all night, scoring 19 points to lead Morehead State over Tennessee-Martin 56-55 Monday night. Morehead State (5-4, 2-1 Ohio Valley Conference) led 56-50 with 1:49 left, and held on as the Skyhawks' McClenon Tolliver missed what would have been a winning layup with less than a second left. Ballard was 7-of-7 from the floor including 3-of-3 3-pointers, and was 2-of-2 from the free throw line. Tennessee-Martin (3-9, 1-2) was led by Cleve Woodfork with 13 points and Gerald Robinson with 12. The Skyhawks stayed in the game by making 26-of-38 free throws to 3-of-10 for the Eagles. Tolliver made the first of two free throws with 12 seconds left to make it 56-55. Quentin Pryor added 12 points for the Eagles.
